-# GNOME Shell
+# GNOME Shell — kierandrewett fork
 
-GNOME Shell provides core user interface functions for the GNOME desktop,
-like switching to windows and launching applications. GNOME Shell takes
-advantage of the capabilities of modern graphics hardware and introduces
-innovative user interface concepts to provide a visually attractive and
-easy-to-use experience.
+This is a personal fork of [GNOME Shell](https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gnome-shell)
+that removes a handful of security/permission gates so the shell can be
+driven and extended more freely from local code. **Don't run this on a
+machine you don't fully trust.** Each gate is in place upstream for a
+reason; this fork accepts the trade-off in exchange for unattended
+automation.
 
-All interactions with the project should follow the [Code of Conduct][conduct].
+Base: upstream tag `49.6`.
+
+## Patches in this fork
+
+### 1. `unsafe-mode` enabled at shell startup
+*File:* `js/ui/main.js`
+
+`global.context.unsafe_mode = true;` is set at the top of `start()`,
+before `_initializeUI()` connects the `notify::unsafe-mode` handler — so
+no "System was put in unsafe mode" notification fires. Effect:
+
+- `org.gnome.Shell.Eval(script)` is callable from any session-bus client,
+  not just Looking Glass. Things like `global.get_pointer()`,
+  `global.display.focus_window`, etc. are readable from a regular script.
+- Any other shell code that gates on `global.context.unsafe_mode` runs in
+  permissive mode.
+
+Upstream guard reference: `if (!global.context.unsafe_mode)` in
+`js/ui/shellDBus.js`, `js/misc/util.js`.
+
+### 2. Extension version validation disabled
+*File:* `js/ui/extensionSystem.js`
+
+`ExtensionManager._isOutOfDate()` now hard-returns `false`. Effect:
+
+- Any extension loads regardless of the `shell-version` field in its
+  `metadata.json`. Equivalent to setting
+  `org.gnome.shell.disable-extension-version-validation = true`
+  permanently, but baked in (so it can't be turned back on by config).
+- Note this only bypasses the in-shell *version* check. The extension
+  still has to be enabled (`gnome-extensions enable <uuid>`) and live in
+  one of the standard search paths.
+
+### 3. Access portal auto-grants every request
+*File:* `js/ui/accessDialog.js`
+
+`AccessDialogDBus.AccessDialogAsync` no longer constructs a modal
+dialog; it returns `(0, {})` immediately (response = OK, no choice
+results). The `DBusSenderChecker` is kept so only the legitimate
+xdg-desktop-portal-gnome frontend and the GNOME RemoteDesktop handover
+can drive it — random session apps still can't call this directly.
+
+This implements `org.freedesktop.impl.portal.Access`, the generic portal
+backend used for "Allow / Deny" prompts. Effect:
+
+- Any portal Access request surfaced through gnome-shell auto-grants.
+- **Note: this does not cover the xdg-desktop-portal ScreenCast source
+  picker.** That dialog lives in `xdg-desktop-portal-gnome` (separate
+  repo). Direct `org.gnome.Mutter.ScreenCast` clients are already
+  unattended (no UI, no portal involvement) — see the `screen-mirror`
+  consumer for an example.
+
+### 4. Version string branded `49.6+kdr`
+*File:* `meson.build`
+
+`project()` version is bumped from `49.6` to `49.6+kdr`. This makes the
+fork visibly identifiable everywhere PACKAGE_VERSION shows up:
+
+- `gnome-shell --version` → `GNOME Shell 49.6+kdr`
+- `org.gnome.Shell.ShellVersion` D-Bus property → `49.6+kdr`
+- Settings → About → GNOME Version → `49.6+kdr`
+
+`PACKAGE_VERSION.split('.')[0]` still returns `"49"`, so any code that
+extracts the major version (e.g. extension downloader URLs) keeps
+working. Extension version validation is bypassed anyway (patch 2), so
+the `+kdr` suffix doesn't disqualify any extensions.
+
+## Building / installing
+
+The accompanying RPM build (`fork-build/` in the consumer repo) applies
+these as patches on the Fedora `gnome-shell` SRPM and produces an
+installable `.rpm`. Recovery if a build breaks the session: drop to a
+TTY (`Ctrl+Alt+F3`), `sudo dnf downgrade gnome-shell`, log back in.
 
